stylometry: When determining the total cost of managing a product in inventory, you must look at the EOQ and the ROP. The costs that are associated with managing inventory include inventory costs, holding/carrying costs, ordering costs, cost of safety stock, and the cost of a stock out. To calculate the Q, you take the square root of 2 times the demand times the cost of ordering divided by the cost of holding. The ROP is calculated by the EEDLT plus the z score times the standard deviation. You want to make sure you do not have too much in inventory where your holding costs are high but you also do not want too little in inventory where your customers are not happy that you do not have it.
